features: Are you tired of storing warnings on your mobile phone? Are you also worried about the lack of internal storage?

【4 IN 1 USB Flash Drive】Compared with the traditional single-plug flash drive, this 1000GB Phone flash drive has multiple plug models and supports devices such as Android (with OTG Function) /Phone/Pad/PC. And just with this compact thumb drive, you can freely transfer photos and videos between multiple devices! Note: Android phones must have OTG function to use this USB flash drive.

【PERFECT to PROTECT INDIVIDUAL PRIVACY】USB Flash Drive 1TB Support to Protect your Personal Data by Password or Fingerprints. And No Need to Worry about Memory Stick will Reveal your Privacy. You can Open Touch ID and Password on setting to secure your whole storage, or Lock selected files with password.

【PHOTO or CONTACT BACKUP at ONE CLICK】One-Click Backup of Photos & Videos from the camera. Free Up Your Phone, Pad, Android Device and PC Data Transfer and Storage More Photos & Videos. Plug to Play and Data Transfer on the Go.

【Format-Friendly Streaming APP】The free "LUV-Share" APP supports all major video and music formats so you can stream directly from the thumb drive, saving you precious space and time (Please scan the QR code to download the app). Memory stick for Phone can backup and restore contacts at one click.
【HIGH SPEED FILE TRANSFERS】Directly plugs into your Phone port and USB port; 80 MB/s reading and 40 MB/s writing speed in USB end. Makes files transmission much easier on the go.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: You can manage photos/videos/files through a dedicated APP (no APP needed when using on Android or Windows PC/MAC/IMAC), which can greatly help you to organize/edit everything and keep the original format for easy searching: One-click backup of photos/videos Automatic backup: photos/videos are taken through the APP camera and automatically saved to the folder. Plug-in and Playback. Play music and movies directly from Photo Stick to IOS phone contacts to backup and restore data privacy: edit and rename and encrypt folders with password or touch ID to share photos/files/videos on different devices (PC/Macbook/IOS phone/tablet). 1) Cross-platform data transfer: 4 ports are designed to easily transfer photos, videos, music and files between iOS devices, Macbook pro / C-type devices, Android phones and computers in a flexible way to meet your needs at any time. 2) Protect your privacy: Make all data protected by password and touch ID, even if you lose the USB flash drive, your privacy will not be stolen. 3) Connect and Play: If you copy MP4 movies from your computer to your device, you can connect it to your IOS phone or Pad and watch the movies directly from your device. 4) Precise compatibility: Video. AVI, DIVX, FLV, M4V, MKV, MOV, MP4, MPG, RM, RMVB, TS, VOB, WMV, 3GP Photo. BMP, TIF, TIFF, PNG, JPG, JPEG, NEF, GIF, HEIC Music. MP3, WAV, M4A, AIFF, AC3, AAC CAF, FLAC, APE files. DOC, DOCX, PPT, PPTX, XLS, XLSX, KEY, NUMBERS, PAGES, PDF, HTML, TXT, RTF.

If you have used iCloud to backup files before, you need to download the files from iCloud to your phone or Pad, and then copy them to your phone USB drive. Due to DRM (Digital Rights Management), we cannot download music or video files from iTunes or by 3rd APP directly to this phone's external memory. USB flash drive is applicable to IOS phone, Android, WINDOWS PC, MACBOOK Note. USB flash drive for iOS needs to download an app "LUV-Share", you can search the app on App Store. (When the phone can't recognize the USB flash drive, you can try to insert the front and back ends of the interface and try a few more times. Or try this. Exit all apps in the background of your phone > Uninstall the "Luv-Share" app > Turn off your phone for a minute and then turn it on > Download the "Luv-Share" app from the App Store > Try to insert the USB flash drive into your phone) If you have backed up files with iCloud before, you need to download the files from iCloud to your phone or Pad and then copy them to the USB flash drive. Android phones need to support OTG function. Most Android devices have OTG function, you can use the USB flash drive directly when you plug it in. File Manager. (The USB flash drive comes with a type-c adapter for the latest Android phones) If your phone doesn't work, you need to open your phone settings to turn on the OTG connection.

Friendly reminder: You cannot transfer or view media files downloaded from iTunes or other third-party applications. This is because these files are protected by digital rights management. If necessary, please remove your phone case before use. This is because the case affects the connection between your phone and the USB flash drive. Even if you insert the USB flash drive into your phone, the USB flash drive may not be recognized by your phone. * FAT32 format is usually suitable for small capacity USB flash drive with better compatibility; for large capacity USB flash drive, it is recommended that the preferred format is: exFAT>FAT32. If the USB flash drive cannot transfer files, you can convert fat32 to exfat format by formatting. *After using the flash drive, make sure to close the applications related to the flash drive and then gently unplug the flash drive so that the files in the flash drive will not be damaged.
Warm Tips: For better experience, please remove your phone case if necessary before using this phone photo stick.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I bought this product because I ran out of space on my IPhone, and could no longer take any more photos. This was a problem that needed to be fixed and the other alternative would’ve been paying for more storage monthly, and I decided that I did not want to spend money every month just to keep my photos on my phone, and that I would prefer to keep my photos on a flash drive anyways to keep my photos in a safe place where I could access them any time. This product was a solution to my problem, and it was so simple to use! All you have to do is download an app on your phone to transfer the photos to the flash drive and you just insert the flash drive right into your phone. It was very easy and now I can transfer photos whenever I want and if I ever want to look back on the photos I downloaded all I have to do is insert it back in my phone or use the opposite side of the flash drive and insert it into a USB plug, like on a computer. I definitely would recommend this for everyone even if you don’t need to free up the space, because it is so nice to have your photos in a safe place!

Happy & Amazed!
